 Child Pools / Wallet Allocations
Manage borrower wallet allocations for fund deployment

On - chain: 0 %

        No borrower wallets configured for this pool's token.

Ask the borrower to register a dedicated wallet for this pool's accepted token.
For this, here as a borrower, i have added one wallet, but it is not visible here in this options



async getBorrowerWalletsForPool(poolId: string) {
    const pool = await this.pools.findOne({ where: { id: poolId } });
    if (!pool) throw new NotFoundException('Pool not found');
    return this.borrowerWallets.find({
        where: { tokenAddress: pool.poolTokenAddress },
    });
}

Here in the borrower wallets, you are fetching the data based on token address, but here you should also add the filter based on the borrower identifier.

